From e3aa419021e80ba8a8fb15f1287ded56107157b0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Julian Zhu <julian.oerv@isrc.iscas.ac.cn>
Date: Mon, 11 May 2026 23:30:12 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] RISC-V: GHASH: Zvbc multi-block aggregation

The initial Zvbc GHASH correctly computes GF(2^128) products via
hardware clmul but processes one block per iteration each time,
leaving register resources underutilized.

Expand on the initial implementation: precompute H^2/H^3/H^4 and
batch 2 or 4 products into shared register pairs before a single
reduction.

Signed-off-by: Julian Zhu <julian.oerv@isrc.iscas.ac.cn>
---
